29 April 2014The Minister of Police Nathi Mthethwa will tomorrow lead a delegation of Ministers in the Justice, Crime Prevention and Security (JCPS) Cluster, as they assess the state of readiness for the general elections in the Rustenburg area, North West. The visit forms part of the continued effort the Ministers started this month to ensure stability ahead of the elections. The visit of the Rustenburg area will take place over two days covering different areas. Today, the Ministers visited Sterkspruit and Molteno in Eastern Cape.Members of the media are invited to join ministers on a community engagement; a walkabout and media briefing at the identified areas. The details are as follows:Date: 30 April 2014 Time: 11:30 Venues: Freedom Park (Next to Shaft 8)Media activity: Community engagement, a walkabout and media briefingGovernment is committed to ensure that a climate for free and fair elections exists in the country on the 7th of May 2014 and wishes to reiterate that it will not tolerate any form of violence, intimidation, incitement, public disorder, vandalism or intolerance in the country.RSVP: Pheliswa Sebati E-mail: pheliswa@gcis.gov.za Cell: 082 413 4609Enquiries: Phumla Williams Cell: 083 501 0139Issued by: GCIS